<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBCFFE66DC2FEA5FE54AA69" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBCFFE66DC2FEA5FE54AA69" blockId="24.[178,1085,312,363]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">
Diagnosis: The 
<typeStatus id="8B7EB2A9FFBCFFE66CD0FEA5FE6CAA4C" box="[416,505,312,334]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">holotype</typeStatus>
has two testaceous fascias on the elytral disc. To date, this is unique in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBCFFE66DC2FEE6FCC1A95C" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBCFFE66DC2FEE6FCC1A95C" blockId="24.[178,1086,379,606]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">
Description: Size: Length 15.0 mm; width 7.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBCFFE66EEAFEE6FC67AA93" box="[922,1010,379,401]" captionStart="Figs 153-156" captionStartId="50.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-60@50.[178,1085,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figs 153-156: Habitus illustrations of (153) Aspitonis undulicornis, holotype; (154) Isoforma biguttula, holotype; (155) I. fritilla, holotype; (156) I. goryi, non-type." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294886/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly testaceous, epicranium and venter brown; pronotum mostly black, upper sides of disc testaceous; elytral disc mostly black, with basal and medial testaceous fasciae. Head: Antennal capitulum very long (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBCFFE66FE0FE4EFD4BAAEB" box="[656,734,467,489]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere longer than funicle; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 25/35. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin linear, not projected at middle; side margins of disc rounded at middle; PW/PL 108/85; elytra conspicuously flared; discal carinae faintly developed; EL/EW 400/110. Abdomen: Female pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
