<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBCFFE66DC2FD25FD48A9E9" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBCFFE66DC2FD25FD48A9E9" blockId="24.[178,1085,696,747]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">
Etymology: The trivial name 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBCFFE66F43FD25FDE1A9CF" box="[563,628,696,717]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">fritilla</emphasis>
is a Latin adjective derived from 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBCFFE66EA4FD25FB8BA9CF" box="[980,1054,696,717]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">fritillus</emphasis>
(= spotted). I refer to the black macula on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
